Summary one: LG has acquired HP's WebOS operating system in a deal to power its smart TV technology.

Summary two: Palm's WebOS operating system, which was created to power smartphones and tablets, has been acquired by HP for $1.2bn (Â£789m). LG will receive the source code, engineers working on it, documentation and the websites promoting it. HP will also hold on to patents underlying WebOS and technology that helps it connect to web-based services. The acquisition is likely driven by LG's recognition that it needs to make gadgets of all types easier to use and the use of core web technology left it well placed for the next generation of mobile apps.

Based on accuracy and conciseness, summary two better summarizes the main points of the passage.
Summary one better summarizes the main points of the passage.
Summary two better summarizes the main points of the passage.
